---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Platform | C-Mind">
  <div class="overflow-hidden bg-white py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-2xl grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-16 sm:gap-y-20 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="lg:pr-8 lg:pt-4">
          <div class="lg:max-w-lg">
            <h2 class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-teal-600">Technology</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">The C-Mind Platform</p>
            <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-600">
              The C-Mind platform uses carefully governed artificial intelligence to support mental health engagement while prioritizing safety, transparency, and clinical alignment.
            </p>
            <dl class="mt-10 max-w-xl space-y-8 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600 lg:max-w-none">
              <div class="relative pl-9">
                <dt class="inline font-semibold text-gray-900">
                  <span class="absolute left-1 top-1 h-5 w-5 text-teal-600 text-lg">‚öôÔ∏è</span>
                  How It Works
                </dt>
                <dd class="inline ml-2">The platform is designed to deliver structured, evidence-informed interactions that adapt to user needs over time, while maintaining clear boundaries regarding diagnosis and treatment.</dd>
              </div>
              <div class="relative pl-9">
                <dt class="inline font-semibold text-gray-900">
                  <span class="absolute left-1 top-1 h-5 w-5 text-teal-600 text-lg">üè•</span>
                  Deployment & Integration
                </dt>
                <dd class="inline ml-2">C-Mind is intended for use in research, pilot, and care-support settings, with configurations that allow integration into existing workflows when appropriate.</dd>
              </div>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
